sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as spark-operator-webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Controller as spark-operator-controller
    participant Driver as Driver Pod<br/>(spark-submit)
    participant Executors as Executor Pods<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Executors: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply SparkApplication<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-sparkapplication<br/>443->9443/TCP, TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate & mutate CR<br/>Inject config, volumes, env vars
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-sparkapplication<br/>443->9443/TCP, TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Response

    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event: SparkApplication created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Driver Pod<br/>HTTPS/443, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Driver: Driver Pod scheduled
    Driver->>K8sAPI: Create Executor Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, spark SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Executors: Executor Pods scheduled
    Driver->>Executors: Task distribution<br/>7078/TCP driver-rpc, 7079/TCP blockmanager
    Executors-->>Driver: Task results

    Note over User,Executors: Flow 2: Spark Connect Session

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply SparkConnect<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event: SparkConnect created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create SparkConnect Server Pod + Service
    Note right of Controller: Service exposes 15002/TCP gRPC
    User->>Driver: gRPC connection<br/>15002/TCP (via Service)
    Driver->>Executors: Task distribution<br/>7078/TCP, 7079/TCP

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    Prometheus->>Webhook: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, No Auth
